O forlorn heart, so pure and unstained, yet so wary to commit,
You wander moonlit corridors where silent reveries sit.
Wounds of old still linger, like dew upon the rose;
You cradle fragile promises where only caution grows.

Yet see—beyond your windowpane, the world is warm and wide;
Love awaits with open arms, and time stands at your side.
Let go the chains of yesterday, and trust what you may find;
For even wary hearts can bloom when hope is unconfined.

O gentle soul, take courage—step softly into light;
The dawn will greet your trembling, and guide you through the night.
